Privacy Policy
Last updated: December 17, 2024
Overview
Advanced JSON Viewer is committed to protecting your privacy. This Safari extension operates entirely within your browser and does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data.
Data Collection
We do not collect any personal information
We do not track your browsing activity
We do not store your JSON data
We do not use cookies or similar tracking technologies
Local Storage
Your settings preferences (like theme choice and font size) are stored locally on your device. This data never leaves your browser and is controlled entirely by you.
Third-Party Services
The extension is distributed through the Apple App Store. Your interaction with the App Store is governed by Apple's privacy policy.
Data Security
All JSON formatting and processing happens locally in your browser. Your data never leaves your device and is not transmitted to any external servers.
Children's Privacy
Our extension does not knowingly collect any personal information from children under 13.
Changes to This Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at
privacy@browserutils.com